.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Given an object, and a set of parameters, this will restrict direct access to the object values, ensuring the object properties can only be modified from within the class/package if necessary.
.PP
This is used in \*(L"new\*(R" in Module::Generic using your module global variable \f(CW\*(C`OBJECT_PERMS\*(C'\fR which should contain a unix permission which is a number from 1 to 7 representing a combinatin of 1 for execution, 2 for write privilege and 4 for read privilege
